Hey Nikolay,
Sorry for the -1. It's both related and not related to your changes in this PS.

It appears that there is a bug in oslo.config in the way it deals with positional args. This may lead to undesired behavior. Basically, oslo.config is parsing positional args in alphabetical order instead of the order in which they appear in the schema. This will result in positional args getting undesired values. Please look a tiny program I wrote to understand this behavior, https://gist.github.com/hmakkapati/cb10bde18a74131c7cb4. Notice the way positional args get mixed up. I spoke to an oslo guy in #openstack-oslo and he confirmed that its a bug. Here is the bug I opened, https://bugs.launchpad.net/oslo.config/+bug/1392428.

Now, coming to my in-line comment about the order of 'command' and 'args'. It doesn't really matter what the order is at this point due to the above mentioned bug. But, once that is fixed, I feel like the order needs to swapped.

Sorry for not mentioning this in the previous PS. I did notice it but I wanted to be sure before I make more noise.

Let me know if it makes sense.
